VALUES (29, 1, E'bwellington', E'laurynw', E'Brian Wellington', 1, E'Civil Engineer', E'bwellington@newfields.com', E'678-697-7439', E'Dr. Wellington is an experienced project engineer with expertise that includes environmental statistics, geostatistics, decision consequence analysis, and GIS analysis. His strengths also encompass planning and design for the management of stormwater on large scale developments, low impact development design, hydrologic modeling, water quality modeling, erosion and sediment control design. Dr. Wellington is an expert on matters relating to Clean Water Act violations, NPDES permits, stormwater management, erosion and sediment control. He earned a BEng with honors from Fourah Bay College, University of Sierra Leone, an MSc in water resources engineering from the University of Dar es Salaam, and a Ph.D. in civil and environmental engineering from Syracuse University. He is licensed in GA.', E'43e78a0d.jpg', E'56a91294.doc', E'', E'', E'', E'', E'2004-10-27', E'2004-10-27', E'404-347-9050 x987', E'Ph.D., PE (GA)', E'0143', 0, 1, NULL);

