VALUES (30, 1, E'mwild', E'mRw4hRw5', E'Michael  Wild', 2, E'Environmental/Civil Engineer', E'mwild@newfields.com', E'404-918-6000', E'Mr. Wild is a specialist in the management, analysis and presentation of environmental data.  He developed the GIS and data management tools that are the foundation of NewFields business model.  He also provides hands-on training for environmental project and technical managers, both internally within NewFields, and with the U.S. Navy Civil Engineer Corps Officer School (CECOS).  He has over 24 years of experience in the environmental field, specializing in geostatistics, decision analysis, water resources and GIS as well as extensive experience in CERCLA and RCRA characterization, remediation, and strategic planning. Mr. Wild has served as an expert or testified in numerous state and federal cases across the county. Mr. Wild earned a B.S. in environmental engineering from the University of Florida and an M.S. in civil engineering from the Georgia Institute of Technology. He is licensed in GA.', E'4fe05d48.jpg', E'Wild Resume2012.pdf', E'', E'', E'', E'mwild@newfields.com', E'2004-10-27', E'2004-10-27', E'404-969-0989', NULL, E'0005', 0, 1, NULL);

