VALUES (35, 6, E'gfrigon', E'password', E'George Frigon', 1, E'Waste Water Specialist', E'gfrigon@newfields.com', E'410-310-1852', E'George Frigon is a senior partner in NewFields and has 40 years of experience.  He is a nationally recognized wastewater treatment expert and co-author of the USEPAâ??s manual for wastewater treatment for small communities. Mr. Frigon brings a practical, yet imaginative approach to water and wastewater treatment.  He has extensive experience in developing metals removal wastewater treatment systems for industry and mining operations that use conventional chemistry, sulfide precipitation, filtration, micro-filtration, ultrafiltration, nano-filtration, reverse osmosis and other processes.  Mr. Frigon has lead the design, modification, and operation of many treatment facilities treating water contaminated by toxic organics and pesticides.  Mr. Frigonâ??s projects have included the design, renovation, and operation of treatment systems that reuse or recycle water or pre-treat for NDPES discharge.  His experience includes the design, construction and operation of systems to produce ultra-pure water for medical and electronics manufacture. Until recently, Mr. Frigon served as Co-Chair of the Advisory Board for the Graduate Part-Time Program in Environmental Engineering and Science at Johns Hopkins University. He received a B.A. in microbiology from University of Connecticut and has masterâ??s level courses in microbiology and the biological sciences at the University of New Haven and Southern Connecticut State University.', E'e42a5e4.jpg', E'c6ef7e8.doc', E'', E'', E'', E'', E'2004-11-01', E'2004-11-01', E'443-546-4144', NULL, E'0134', 0, 1, NULL);

