VALUES (45, 9, E'smattingly', E'tigger', E'Stephen Mattingly (Steve)', 1, E'Environmental Chemist', E'smattingly@newfields.com', E'781-264-7081', E'Mr. Emsbo-Mattingly specializes in the diagnostic measurement of tar, wood preservatives, PCBs, petroleum, and industrial products in water, soil, sediment, and air. He offers extensive experience in manufactured gas plants, chemical plants, wood treating facilities, tar refineries, petroleum storage facilities, chlorinated solvent industries, and urban background. During his 20 years in the environmental industry, Mr. Emsbo-Mattingly has helped pioneer forensic methods for tar, PCBs and vapor intrusion investigations, and has assisted in source identification, environmental laboratory data review, quality control assessments, statistical analysis and graphics production for numerous projects. Mr. Emsbo-Mattingly earned a B.A. in biology from Oberlin College and an M.S. in environmental science from the University of Massachusetts.', E'1331770f.jpg', E'48528372.doc', E'Steve (NewFields Boston)', E'', E'', E'smattingly@newfields.com', E'2004-11-01', E'2004-11-01', E'781-681-5040 x103', E'MS', E'0180', 0, 1, NULL);

