VALUES (48, 9, E'kmccarthy', E'password', E'Kevin McCarthy', 1, E'Chemist', E'kmccarthy@newfields.com', E'781-264-7077', E'Mr. McCarthy has more than 23 years of experience in environmental forensic chemistry. He specializes in environmental forensics of non-aqueous phase liquids (NAPL), waters, soils/sediments, and soilborne and airborne vapors. An expert in forensic chemical fingerprinting, Mr. McCarthy provides detailed chemical analysis, interpretation and characterization of petroleum products and manufactured gas plant residues and wastes. He has managed and written interpretive reports for hundreds of projects delineating the fate and transport of petroleum based hydrocarbons and coal-derived wastes in aquatic and terrestrial environments. In addition, he has authored or coauthored more than 50 scientific papers. Mr. McCarthy received a B.S. from Westfield State College.', E'599596f6.jpg', E'fb41206.doc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, E'2004-11-01', E'2004-11-01', E'781-681-5040 x104', NULL, E'0181', 0, 1, NULL);

