VALUES (221, 48, E'jqword', E'Tylodina1', E'Jack Q. Word', 1, E'Environmental Scientist, Toxicologist', E'jqword@newfields.com', E'360-808-7705', E'Dr. Word offers clients a strong technical understanding of environmental systems, combined with worldwide consulting experience and the capabilities of\r\na nationally recognized biological testing laboratory. The lab provides clients with innovative solutions and produces cost-effective treatment strategies to facilitate working within regulatory constraints.  Dr. Wordâ??s unique skills provide a basis for separating true environmental problems from other contributing factors that produce adverse ecological results. In an ongoing project in Brazil, Dr. Word has been instrumental in identifying and segregating ecological effects attributable to a pesticide manufacturing plant. His efforts have helped to narrow the human health impacts from the entire site to a much smaller area involved with chemical compound synthesis. Dr. Word earned a B.S. in zoology and an M.A. in biology from California State University at Long Beach, followed by a Ph.D. in fisheries from University of Washington.', NULL, E'7b653bf.doc', E'', E'', E'', E'', E'2007-03-29', E'2007-03-29', E'360-297-6040', E'Ph.D.', E'0305', 0, 1, NULL);

