VALUES (222, 48, E'bgardiner', E'password', E'Bill Gardiner', 1, E'Environmental Scientist', E'bgardiner@newfields.com', E'360-204-1286', E'Mr. Gardiner has over 20 years of experience in evaluating the effects of contaminants in the aquatic and marine environments under a variety of national and international regulatory settings.  Mr. Gardiner specializes in refining estimates of bioavailability, effects, and risk by integrating field and laboratory based site-specific biological and chemical data.  Through an understanding of multiple environmental factors that affect contaminant-receptor pathways, Mr. Gardiner has been able to separate the effects of confounding factors from those of site-related chemicals of potential concern.  Mr. Gardiner has conducted numerous environmental evaluations of hazardous waste sites, dredged materials, petroleum-related compounds, and a variety of contaminant and non-contaminant stressors.  He specializes in project management, marine, estuarine, and freshwater toxicology, ecological evaluation, restoration, and scientific diving and sample collection.  Mr. Gardiner has a B.S. in zoology from the University of Washington and an M.S. in environmental toxicology from Western Washington University.', E'488935d5.jpg', E'23cded88.doc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, E'2007-03-29', E'2007-03-29', E'360-297-6040', NULL, E'0308', 0, 1, NULL);

