VALUES (414, 70, E'klyncoln', E'boomer214', E'Karen Lyncoln', 1, E'Senior Social & Health Impact Assessment Scientist', E'klyncoln@newfields.com', E'406-210-1206', E'Ms. Lyncoln has more than 37 years of experience preparing social, economic, and health studies related to environmental projects, public involvement, and land use planning. She has significant experience preparing National Environmental Policy Act (NEPA) compliance documents and designing and implementing public opinion surveys for engineering and environmental projects. She has developed environmental justice programs for the last 16 years and has extensive experience working with Native American and Hispanic communities and rural populations throughout the world. Ms. Lyncoln has prepared the social, economic and health baseline and impact analyses for projects involving mining, oil and gas development, water diversions, well field development, rights-of-way transfer, land withdrawals, airports, and scientific laboratory facilities in the United States, Peru, Ghana, and Indonesia. Ms. Lyncoln has worked directly with industry as well as with federal and state natural resource, environmental, and energy agencies. Ms Lyncoln has a B.A. in Urban Studies from San Francisco State University.', E'', E'Karen Linsley Lyncoln resume.pdf', E'', E'', E'', E'', E'2010-10-25', E'2010-10-25', E'907-717-5732', NULL, E'0635', 0, 1, NULL);

