VALUES (417, 67, E'jjohnson', E'600jeff', E'Jeffrey Johnson', 1, E'Associate', E'jjohnson@newfields.com', E'281-838-5935', E'Dr. Jeffrey A. Johnson is a recognized expert in groundwater flow, and contaminant transport and fate. He has over 30 years of professional experience in natural resource assessment, site characterization, remedial operations, and technical analyses. He has extensive technical skills in groundwater flow, contaminant transport, and fate of both dissolved and free-phase plumes. For the past 10 years, he has worked extensively in the characterization and remediation of LNAPL and DNAPL sites. Dr. Johnson is experienced in developing characterization programs to delineate natural hydrocarbon sources, such as coal bed methane and oil seeps, from anthropogenic releases. He is experienced in computer applications including analytical and numerical models, GIS, and 3D visual imagery. He has supported numerous technical organizations, committees, and groups including API, ASTM, and RTDF. He holds a Ph.D. in Geology from the University of California, Berkeley and is a AIPG Certified and Registered Professional Geologist. He is registered in AR and SC.', E'', E'Johnson Jeffrey_CV_JJ_1_14_L.pdf', E'', E'', E'', E'', E'2011-01-14', E'2011-01-14', E'713-357-5244', E'Ph.D., Registered Geologist Texas, South Carolina, Arkansas, AIPG certification, ASTM', E'0490', 0, 1, NULL);

